DEMOBILIZE
  Convert active military in sectors into civilians.

SYNTAX
  demobilize <sects> <amount> [reserve|civ]
  demo       <sects> <amount> [reserve|civ]

DESCRIPTION
  Converts sector military into civilians. Costs $5 per troop.

  <sects>   - sector(s) to draw from
  <amount>  - how many to demobilize per sector.
              Use a negative number to keep that many and demob rest.
              Example: -10 means "keep 10, demob the rest"
  reserve   - (default) demobilized troops become civilians AND are
              also credited to your national reserve pool
  civ       - demobilized troops become civilians only, no reserve
              credit

  Demobilized mil ALWAYS become civilians in the sector they're
  demobilized from — that's the core effect in both modes. The
  reserve/civ choice only controls whether they're ALSO added to
  the national reserve on top of that; reserve is a separate
  callback pool, not an alternative destination for the troops.

  Requirements:
    - Sector must be >=60% efficient
    - Sector must still be under original ownership (not conquered)
    - You must have enough money ($5/troop)
    - Civilian count is capped at 9999 per sector; demobilization
      into an already-full sector demobilizes fewer than requested

  The reserve can then be spent via 'enlist' to quickly deploy
  troops anywhere you own.

EXAMPLE
  demobilize 1,-3 100       100 mil -> civs at 1,-3, +100 reserve, cost $500
  demobilize * -10          keep 10 mil each sector, rest -> civs + reserve
  demobilize 0,0 50 civ     convert 50 mil to civilians only, no reserve
  demo * 200                shorthand alias

